Introduction

Lee Si An is a South Korean model and former Kpop trainee, currently signed under Leaders Entertainment. Known for her previous career as an aspiring idol, she first gained public attention as a contestant on the survival show Idol School in 2017, where she ranked 16th in the finale, preventing her from debuting with the girl group fromis_9.

A year later, Si An returned to the Kpop scene by participating in the hit survival show Produce 48, where she was eliminated in episode 11, finishing 30th. Despite not achieving a debut from the show, her time in the Kpop industry led to her involvement in multiple pre-debut projects, including a stint under Stone Music Entertainment and a short period as a trainee with HF Music Company. She was also connected to the pre-debut girl group Happyface Girls under Happyface Entertainment (now Dreamcatcher Company) in 2021, but the group disbanded before debuting.

Transitioning to a modeling career in 2022, Si An signed with Leaders Entertainment, focusing on advertisement modeling. She has worked with notable brands such as Samsung Galaxy, FILA, New Balance, and COSRX, and is recognized for her work with athleisure brands.

Additionally, Si An gained further attention with her appearance on Single's Inferno Season 4, where her past as a Kpop trainee was highlighted, drawing interest from fans who had previously supported her during her idol career.
